SpatialPrimaryFSEvalGrouper
public class PrimaryFSEvalGrouper
extends EvaluationGrouper

This EvaluationGrouper evaluates each individual in the primary subpopulation individually against a random (but fixed-size) set of individuals chosen from the entire Population. Fitnesses are *only* set for individuals in the primary subpopulation.

ruppmatt

next

public EvaluationGroup next(ec.EvolutionState state,
                            int calling_thread,
                            int for_evaluation_thread)
For each individual in the primary subpopulation, create an Evaluation Group. Only the individual in the primary subpopulation being focused on has its fitness evaluated. All peers in the group are randomly selected by the configuration settings and will not have their fitnesses re-evaluated.

Specified by:
next in class EvaluationGrouper
Parameters:

threadnum -
Returns:
an EvaluationGroup or null if empty
